title: North America Free Trade Agreement (NAFTA) Basics - Video #8
description: NAFTA allows your company to ship most goods to customers in Canada and Mexico duty free as long as they are comprised mostly of U.S. components. This video covers the key parts of the agreement and introduces the process for obtaining the benefits.  For more information, please visit our website: http://www.census.gov/foreign-trade/
tags: NAFTA', 'Free Trade Agreements', 'Certificates of Origin', 'Exporting', 'Doing Business in Canada', 'Doing Business in Mexico', 'Tariff', 'U.S. Commercial Service'
